---

## What the Vertical Teaches

The *terroir* of Les Amoureuses is unmistakable across every vintage: that iron-mineral backbone, the violet-rose aromatic signature, the precision of the acidity. What changes is **weight** and **time**.

- **Hot years** (2015, 2018) give richness — the vineyard softens them into elegance.
- **Cool years** (2016, 2019) give tension — the vineyard sharpens them into focus.
- **Middle years** (2017) give joy — the vineyard keeps them honest.

> The vineyard is the constant. The vintage is the variable. The sommelier's job is to know which one you're drinking for tonight.

